Jason Garner (jgarner@netcom.com) wrote:
: Would it be possible to write a program that would work on top of
: existing modem programs like TELIX which, upon connecting to another
: system/BBS (whatever), send a PGP public key and have the other system
: do the same?  And then encrypt all of the data with those keys and
: have it decrypted at both ends before giving the cleartext output
: to the modem program?  Then anyone trying to tap the data would only
: see PGP encrypted text being sent.  Does PGP encrypt/decrypt at
: 57.6 Kbps?  I'd post the question to alt.security.pgp but
: someone would probably attack the question and tell me that this
: has already been discussed in a FAQ (without telling me where that FAQ is 
: to be found, of course).
: -Jason


	I don't know. It wouldn't be using PGP, however. What you would 
do is use an RSA key pair to generate a session key for some bulk 
algorithm, such as IDEA, DES, etc. A good implementation aught to be able 
to do it at 57.6Kbps, on a fast computer.
	Hurricane

